“Developing the book and putting that all together was one hell of a job. We had a big team around us, we had a food editor assisting, putting in a little less chef talk and making the recipes a little bit softer and more approachable for the people at home.

“People that know me know that I’m very impatient. When I want something, I probably wanted it yesterday not today, so I put that pressure on myself trying to get things right, particularly with photoshoots.” @chef.mattabe 

Showcasing more than 25 years of continued success, Restaurant Gordon Ramsay: A Story of Excellence offers an intimate look behind the scenes at one of the world’s best restaurants, its evolution, and the stories of @gordongram, Matt Abé and the @restaurantgordonramsay team who have strived for perfection at the three Michelin-starred culinary institution.
 
We have two signed copies to give away, to be in with a chance to win head over to the full article on The Staff Canteen website, link in our bio. You need to sign up for FREE before you enter because this is a members only competition!

Following the overwhelming success of last year, our collaboration with three Michelin-starred @restaurantgordonramsay is back on their menu this Game Season!
 
Chef Patron, @chef.mattabe created his dish after tasting our whiskey, The Taoscán, and knew that he would love to use one of our Single Malts in a dish. Matt noted that the “flavour, complexity and different layers” of The Donn complement perfectly the Aynhoe Park Fallow Deer, pickled blackberries and beetroot in his dish 🥃
 
We invite you to experience this incredible fusion of our whiskey and cuisine from one of the finest chefs in the world. Click on the link in our bio to make your reservation now whilst it’s available 📲

Born in Australia and making waves in Britain’s fine-dining scene, we are honoured to see Chef Matt Abé serve his ‘grass fed, 60-day dry aged beef with Jerusalem artichoke, crones, and black garlic’ ⭐⭐⭐

In 2009, Matt joined the three Michelin-starred Restaurant Gordon Ramsay and after four years was promoted to Chef de Cuisine, leading the kitchen team. In September 2020, he became the Chef Patron of the restaurant, overseeing the successful management of one of the most famous restaurants in the world, holding three Michelin stars since 2001. 

Matt is known worldwide for his exceptional attention to detail, intense passion for his craft and creative flair that is utterly inspiring.
